  "body": "The following tests which are under `BlockchainTests/InvalidBlocks` seem to contain completely valid chains at least for Istanbul.\r\n\r\n    `timestampTooLow_Istanbul`\r\n    `timestampTooHigh_Istanbul`\r\n    `wrongStateRoot_Istanbul` (from bcUncleHeaderValidity)\r\n    `incorrectUncleTimestamp4_Istanbul`\r\n    `incorrectUncleTimestamp5_Istanbul`\r\n    `futureUncleTimestamp3_Istanbul`\r\n\r\nThese tests pass without raising any exceptions when running through the `retesteth` [tool](http://retesteth.ethdevops.io/web/index.php)\r\n\r\nEdit:- I think the `bcUncleHeaderValidity/correct.json` file also does not belong among the `InvalidBlocks` tests. (Also see [legacy tests issue](https://github.com/ethereum/legacytests/issues/2))\r\n\r\n",
